  "task": "Implement Byzantine-resilient consensus (v18) extending v17 with: (1) Threshold Cryptography with Proactive Secret Sharing—validators must implement t-of-n threshold signatures where private key shares rotate across validators every R rounds via verifiable secret sharing (VSS), ensuring no coalition ≤t can ever reconstruct the consensus key; agents must prove that after every rotation, all previous key material is cryptographically erased and new shares are distributionally independent; (2) Adaptive Byzantine Leader Election—implement leader selection that detects Byzantine leaders (those who equivocate, censor, or delay messages >Δ slots) and triggers atomic leader replacement without consensus stalls; agents must prove leader replacement happens within 4 message delays and maintains quorum continuity; (3) Censorship-Resistant Transaction Ordering via Commit-Reveal—transactions must be committed (hashed, encrypted to leader) before proposal phase, then revealed; agents must detect censoring leaders (those omitting valid commits) and trigger immediate revocation; prove censorship detection occurs within 3 message delays and rejected commits eventually get included; (4) Synchrony Verification with Dynamic Parameter Adjustment—agents must measure actual network synchrony (via timestamped echo rounds), adjust consensus timeouts (Δt_new = 2×measured_latency_p99), and detect asynchronous partitions; if partition suspected, enter Byzantine-tolerant async mode; prove adaptive adjustment prevents both false positives (<5% timeout waste) and missed deadlines.",
